In this article, President Barack Obama sends a letter to the Chairman (or Chairwoman) of the Congress, stating that he has determined and reported that the suspension of the right to bring an action under title III of the Cuban Liberty and Democratic Solidarity (LIBERTAD) Act of 1996 is necessary for the national interests of the United States. This suspension is to last for 6 months beyond February 1, 2013, and it is intended to expedite a transition to democracy in Cuba. The letter is signed by Barack Obama.